{{about|values from ''Minecraft: Java Edition'' since Java Edition 1.13|values until Java Edition 1.12.2|Java Edition pre-flattening data values|values from Classic|Java Edition Classic data values|values from Indev|Java Edition Indev data values}}
{{exclusive|java}}

These '''data values''' refer to the different types of blocks, items and other features on {{el|je}} and are used in many places in ''Minecraft''. [[#Blocks|Block IDs]] are used to define blocks placed in the world. [[#Items|Item IDs]] are valid only for items (including items in chests and items dropped in the world). All block IDs that do not have a gray background in this page are also valid item IDs. There are also [[#Entities|entity IDs]] for entities such as mobs and projectiles.

{{TOC|right}}

== IDs ==
These IDs are in the [[resource location]] format, with their [[Resource location#minecraft namespace|{{code|minecraft}} namespace]] omitted. The game accepts these [[resource location]]s either with or without the {{code|minecraft:}} prefix.
